name: cred-rea-fish-team-belt-transect-survey-at-ofu-olosega-islands-2004
notes: Belt transects along 3 consecutively-placed, 25m transect lines were surveyed as part of Rapid Ecological Assessments conducted at 9 sites at Ofu and Olosega Islands in American Samoa in February, 2004 from the NOAA vessel Oscar Elton Sette (OES04-02). Raw survey data included species level abundance estimates.
